                            <comment id="13648523" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 16:01:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve already fixed this in 2.0 by moving level information into sstable metadata (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4872&quot; title=&quot;Move manifest into sstable metadata&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4872&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4872&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), but it may be reasonable to add an fsync to 1.2.  What do you think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=krummas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;krummas&quot;&gt;krummas&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13648524" author="krummas" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 16:04:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yeah sounds good, ill fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13648663" author="krummas" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 18:37:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fsyncs the file after flushing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13648933" author="carlyeks" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 23:55:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. The patch doesn&apos;t apply to the 1.1 branch; I&apos;m sure it will be easy to fix up so that it does, assuming this is target to 1.1 and 1.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13649014" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 4 May 2013 05:09:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(setting affects-version to when this was introduced)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13649140" author="krummas" created="Sat, 4 May 2013 18:59:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed as fe910e6c90d81cc61c16859bcef9f0dcb42cc827, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
